Package org.cytoscape.dyn.internal.event

Interface Summary
DynEvent DynEvent is the interface for the Callable event that is used to generate graph events between a Source and a Sink.
Filter<T> Filter filters event that pass between a a Source and a Sink.
Sink<T> Sink receives graph events (elements and attributes), but does not contain a graph instance.
Source<T> Source produces graph events (elements and attributes), but does not contain a graph instance.
 

Class Summary
CreateEdgeAttrDynEvent<T> CreateEdgeAttrDynEvent implements the interface DynEvent for the generation of edge attribute events.
CreateEdgeDynEvent<T> CreateEdgeDynEvent implements the interface DynEvent for the generation of edge events.
CreateGraphAttrDynEvent<T> CreateGraphAttrDynEvent implements the interface DynEvent for the generation of graph attribute events.
CreateGraphDynEvent<T> CreateGraphDynEvent implements the interface DynEvent for the generation of graph events.
CreateNodeAttrDynEvent<T> CreateNodeAttrDynEvent implements the interface DynEvent for the generation of node attribute events.
CreateNodeDynEvent<T> CreateNodeDynEvent implements the interface DynEvent for the generation of node events.
